<HEAD>Forbes 400 List of Wealthiest Americans</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Forbes Richest, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is Forbes magazine's 1990 list of the 400
richest Americans in descending order of wealth, showing estimated
fortune in millions, residence, source of wealth and age.
   1. John Werner Kluge, $5,600, Charlottesville, Va., Metromedia,
76.
   2. Warren Edward Buffett, $3,343, Omaha, Neb., stock market, 60.
   3. Ronald Owen Perelman, $2,87, New York City, leveraged
buyouts, 47.
   4. Henry Lea Hillman, $2,650, Pittsburgh, industrialist, 71.
   5. Barbara Cox Anthony, $2,600, Honolulu, inheritance (Cox
Enterprises), 67.
   6. Anne Cox Chambers, $2,600, Atlanta, inheritance (Cox
Enterprises), 70.
   7. Samuel Irving Newhouse Jr., $2,600, New York City,
publishing, 62.
   8. Donald Edward Newhouse, $2,600, New York City, publishing,
61.
   9. Jay Arthur Pritzker, $2,500, Chicago, financier, 68.
   10. Robert Alan Pritzker, $2,500, Chicago, financier, 64.
   11. Sam Moore Walton, $2,500, Bentonville, Ark., Wal-Mart
Stores, 72.
   12. S. Robson Walton, $2,500, Bentonville, Ark., inheritance
(Wal-Mart Stores), 46.
   13. John T. Walton, $2,500, San Diego, inheritance (Wal-Mart
Stores), 45.
   14. Jim C. Walton, $2,500, Bentonville, Ark., inheritance
(Wal-Mart Stores), 42.
   15. Alice L. Walton, $2,500, Rogers, Ark., inheritance (Wal-Mart
Stores), 41.
   16. William Henry Gates III, $2,500, Seattle, Microsoft Corp.,
34.
   17. Henry Ross Perot, $2,200, Dallas, electronic data
management, 60.
   18. A. Alfred Taubman, $2,100, Bloomfield Hills, Mich., real
estate, 65.
   19. Ted Arison, $2,100, Miami Beach, Fla., cruise ships, 66.
   20. Sumner Murray Redstone, $2,000, Newton Centre, Mass., movie
theaters, 67.
   21. Charles de Ganahl Koch, $1,900, Wichita, Kan., inheritance,
54.
   22. David Hamilton Koch, $1,900, New York City, inheritance (oil
services), 50.
   23. Edgar Miles Bronfman, $1,900, New York City, Seagram Co.,
61.
   24. Charles F. Feeney, $1,900, London, Duty Free Shoppers, 59.
   25. Leslie Herbert Wexner, $1,800, Columbus, Ohio, The Limited
Inc., 53.
   26. Forrest Edward Mars Sr., $1,700, Las Vegas, candy, 80s.
   27. Forrest Edward Mars Jr., $1,700, McLean, Va., candy, 59.
   28. John Franklyn Mars, $1,700, Arlington, Va., candy, 55.
